headline: How Home Depot’s GMS Bid Impacts Its Stock Price After a 69% Five Year Rally
summary: If you have been watching Home Depot stock lately and wondering whether it is time to jump in, hold tight, or take some profits, you are not alone. With shares closing at $406.77 and up an impressive 69.3% over the past five years, it is no wonder investors are talking. Even this year, the stock has added 4.7% since January and gained 8.9% over the last month alone, although it pulled back slightly by 1.5% in just the last week. That kind of short-term volatility tends to spark questions...
